Good Joke:Word Count Ratio
{{Styleguide}} 
Here in [[Encyclopedia Dramatica|ED]], we use the '''Good Joke:Word Count Ratio''' formula to judge whether articles are [[funny]] or [[unfunny]].  

==How to calculate==
#Copy and paste the article into your favorite word-processing software.
#Do a word count
#Read the article.
##For every good joke, award 1 point.
##For every [[lulz]], award 1 point.
##Add the two scores.
##For every verified [[fact]], subtract 1 point.
#Simplify (good joke + lulz - fact) : (word count)
#You have the ratio!

==What to do if you find an article with a bad ratio==
Give it [[:template:unfunny|<nowiki>{{unfunny}}</nowiki>]] (users) or [[:template:crap|<nowiki>{{crap}}</nowiki>]] (any article or user) as applicable.  If you turn an article into not-crap, please change the [[:template:crap|<nowiki>{{crap}}</nowiki>]] template to [[:template:notcrap|<nowiki>{{notcrap}}</nowiki>]].

